Actually, this does kind of bring up an interesting question...<br>
<br>
Is there a &quot;best&quot; application of alt advance points?   I would say there are several Paths of AltXP depending on what type of groups you hunt in, whether you raid a lot, and what your roles are....<br>
<br>
I think we can agree it starts with<br>
Run speed x3<br>
Natural regen x3<br>
<br>
but there the simplicity stops.<br>
Combat fury?   Damage avoidance?  mitigation? fearless?  Mental clarity?   <br>
<br>
Knowing what we know now, should we have a general conscensus on Altxp?  Possibly for the following paths<br>
<br>
-Combat Tank, Small group xp raiding, casual gamer Paladin<br>
-Solo'er, less than 1 group player<br>
-Raid oriented guild - possible secondary tank, damage dealer<br>
-raid guild - backup healer, chanter protecter, Cheal rotation protection<br>
-Generalist - xp grouping, group with friends, varied roll  (this is similar to the combat tank, but will likely balance melee and caster sides equally)<br>
<br>
<br>
I will have to sit down and go through the list to try to create this, but those who have many of the Archtype and Class skills would be better able, since they have many of the skills.<br>
